<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Posted this on the TL forum... thought some of you might like to read it....<P>#@#@#@#@#@#@#@#@#@#@#@#@#@@##@#@#@#@@#<P>My only issue is this... the Minstrel need never spec beyond getting the first charm, and they can master level 55+ humanoids. It takes NO dedication for them to charm much higher pets than us. If we dedicate our whole lives to Mind spec, the only thing we get is a more reliable, lower level pet.<P>Just seems to devalue our charming abilities......<P>And as many have pointed out, the number of MOBs that are NOT undead, giant, dragon, or the other non-charmable types that are above level 40 are again slim pickings.Examples....<P>(Note, this has changed since the PRIMA guide, but not drastically so in most cases)<P>MAGICAL:<BR>Smallest category available.<BR>Stone Sentinel is 48-50<BR>Everything else is 37 or lower<BR>or level 52 or higher...<P>GREAT for Minstrels, useless for us.<P>INSECT:<BR>Also a small category<BR>Cliff Crawler is 42-45<BR>38 is the next highest, with most under 20<BR>This would be a great addendum early, but helps little once we get the spell to use it.<P>Animal is the one that will help us most.<P>ANIMAL:<BR>Great Boar and Rock Bounder can be up to 46<BR>There are two others in the 40's<P>Everything else is under this. But since we get this one fairly early it will help most.<P>So with full spec we will hit Insect at 14 and Magical at level 20. So a total of 16 new pet types are added to our arsenal amonst insect and magical IF we focus 100% on mind. If we go 2/3 mind the useful pets in those categories drops to about 8 total. Magical is only a useful category if you can charm a pet over level 50.<P>So take all these others away from sorcerors. Follow the theme of our epic quest. I say at level 20 we get undead! That is when our quest starts dealing with necromancy the most. Let the songs of others soothe the savage beast, and let us learn the words to dominate the dead in order to destroy that very evil!<P>I know people want giant, but it is actually useless to us also. We would not get it till well past level 20, so it woudl add maybe 3 more pets available. Elemental is ALL too low level to be worthwhile.<P>Reptiles makes more sense than Insect and would add more pets, and trees are a good range but make NO sense whatsoever.<P>ONLY undead would make us useful in a large range of zones and scenarios. ONLY undead would make us useful in the many dungeons of the land. ONLY undead is actually logical to the theme of the Sorceror, and within the back story of the class.<P>So if it were a vote, i woudl GLADLY give up all other charm extra types if we got undead at level 20. Level 20 is where the hurt starts for us, it is where our quest story start directly interacting with necromancy, and it is the only one that woudl make us have useful pets for the remainer of our career.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
</FONT>
