<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I'd be willing to make a bet that any animal/insect/magical mobs that have been added since the Prima Strategy Guide was published are offset by mobs that are listed in the Guide, but have never been in the game.<P>Has anyone ever seen these mobs?<P>ANIMAL<BR>Bloodfish<BR>Blue Gill<BR>Werewolf Churl<P>INSECT<BR>Frenetic Wolfspider<BR>Large Wolfspider<BR>Tree Spider<BR>Wolfspider<P>MAGICAL<BR>Werewolf Bodyguard<BR>Werewolf Noble<BR>Werewolf Scruff<BR>Wolfaur Lunarian<BR>Wolfaur Pragmatic<BR>Wolfaur Quixot<P>I have not.<P>I maintain that replacing the ability to charm Animal/Insect/Magical mobs with the ability to charm Undead mobs (of which there are an equal number as Humanoid mobs, and of similar level ranges, 1-50) would be much more useful to us, and logical in DAOC's context.<P>Animals and Insects are too stupid.  In order to charm something, it is more realistic if that creature has some amount of intelligence.  Otherwise it's just a pet.  Leave that for the lesser realms.<P>--------------------<P><B>Baelzar<BR>50th Level Sorceror<BR>Redemption<BR>Iseult/Albion</B>
